  <h1>
   cos
  </h1>
  In a right angled triangle
  <i>
   cos(val) = Adjacent / Hypotenuse
  </i>
  where val is one of the three angles. This function will always return a number between 1 and -1.
  <strong>
   NOTE
  </strong>
  : This function takes a value in radians not degrees.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">cos(val);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      val
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The angle (in radians) to return the cosine of.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">val = cos( 0 );
</code></pre>
  This will set val to 1.
 </body>
